      "message": "When you split this into two tests, I\u0027d recommend just doing\n\ngot, err :\u003d Properties(ctx)\nrequire.NoError(t, err)\n...\n\nA mix of require and assert here keeps things clean, as require will stop execution if that error is returned (and thus we don\u0027t want to assert anything on got), and having (possibly multiple asserts) is nice to get clarity on all the things that are wrong with the output, which I generally find better for debugging.\n\n(here and other places)",
